This is a sample application to store to do list using the mean(mongoDb, Express, AngularJS and Node.js) technology stack.
This is a single page application where you can add the things you want to complete and maintain a ToDo list.
Once a given task is complete, you can strike it off by clicking on the mark as complete button againt the task.
This will delete the task from your list leaving only the undone tasks.

To run this application, download the project folder from https://github.com/sshubha/meanstack
navigate to the meanstack folder after download.
run the command:
>> npm install

After the successfull completion of the above command, run the following command:
>> node server.js

Once you get the message that the server is successfull started on port 8080,
access the application using the url: http://localhost:8080/